1. Linear Search is the simplest searching algorithm.
2. It traverses the array sequentially to locate the required element.
3. Time Complexity - O(n)
Algorithm :-

1.LinearSearch(A,Key)
2. {
3. i := 1
4. while i <= n and A[i] != Key do,
5.   do i++
6. if i <= n,    return True
7. else          return False
8. }

Best - case Time Complexity :- O(1) --> If the key value or the target value is at the first position.
Worst - case Time Complexity :- O(n) --> If the key value is at the last position of the array (or) the key value 
      is not present in the array.
